gsvc-mount is NOT vendored: it is the private mount core and its source must never be copied into
this public tree. crates/gsvc-mount here is a resolution-only placeholder (a `compile_error!` lib
plus a tensorlake-adapted Cargo.toml) so the public repo builds offline with no access to the
artifact_storage repo. It is consumed only by tensorlake-cli behind the optional `mount` feature,
so default builds never compile it.

Official mount-enabled binaries are built with `just build-cli-mount`, which copies the real
gsvc-mount src/ from a sibling artifact_storage checkout over the placeholder for the duration of
the build (using the placeholder's adapted Cargo.toml) and restores the placeholder afterward.
Keep the placeholder Cargo.toml's dependency list in sync with the real crate's.
